  "translations": {
    "en": "lightning. He said: My God! What is the reward of one who is patient upon the harm and the insults of the people for Your sake? He said: I will assist them in the horrors of the Day of Resurrection. He said: My God! What is the reward of one whose eyes fill with tears out of humility before You? He said: O Musa! I will protect his face from the heat of the Fire, and I will protect him on the Great Day of Dismay. He said: My God! What is the reward of one who abandons betrayal out of shyness before You? He said: O Musa! He will have protection on the Day of Resurrection. He said: My God! What is the reward of one who loves those who obey You? He said: O Musa! I will prohibit him from My Fire. He said: O My God! What is the recompense of one who purposely kills a believer? He said: I will not look to him on the Day of Resurrection, nor will I dismiss his falter. He said: M",
